<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1007,1952,2015]" box="[151,1007,1988,2015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1988,2015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[314,378,1988,2014]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Spain</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[432,527,1988,2014]" name="Portugal" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Portugal</collectingCountry>
only (
<bibRefCitation author="Patiny, S." box="[598,750,1988,2015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref22024" refString="Patiny, S. (2012 a) Atlas of the European Bees: genus Flavipanurgus. STEP Project, Atlas Hymenoptera, Mons, Belgium. Available from: http: // www. zoologie. umh. ac. be // hymenoptera / page. asp? ID = 24 (accessed 12 March 2020)" type="url" year="2012">Patiny 2012a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cross, I. &amp; Wood, T. J." box="[762,995,1988,2015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" pagination="563 - 572" refId="ref20735" refString="Cross, I. &amp; Wood, T. J. (2018) New data on the Iberian endemic bee genus Flavipanurgus Warncke (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Andrenidae): Ecological and genomic data reveal a hidden species. Zootaxa, 4521 (4), 563 - 572. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.4.5" type="journal article" year="2018">Cross &amp; Wood 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,152,359]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,153,179]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Notes:</emphasis>
Originally described from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[646,711,152,178]" name="Georgia" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Iberia</collectingCountry>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Warncke, 1972)" baseAuthorityName="Warncke" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[937,1402,152,179]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavipanurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibericus">
<emphasis box="[937,1200,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Flavipanurgus ibericus</emphasis>
(Warncke, 1972)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Warncke" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavipanurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kastiliensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">F. kastiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was raised to species status by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cross, I. &amp; Wood, T. J." box="[682,931,188,215]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" pagination="563 - 572" refId="ref20735" refString="Cross, I. &amp; Wood, T. J. (2018) New data on the Iberian endemic bee genus Flavipanurgus Warncke (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Andrenidae): Ecological and genomic data reveal a hidden species. Zootaxa, 4521 (4), 563 - 572. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.4.5" type="journal article" year="2018">Cross &amp; Wood (2018)</bibRefCitation>
due to distinct genetic, dietary, and distributional differences. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Warncke" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[410,707,224,250]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavipanurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kastiliensis">
<emphasis box="[410,707,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Flavipanurgus kastiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an oligolege of 
<taxonomicName box="[924,999,224,250]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[924,999,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Sedum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1168,224,251]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Crassulaceae</taxonomicName>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Warncke" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[1289,1408,224,250]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavipanurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibericus">
<emphasis box="[1289,1408,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">F. ibericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an oligolege of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[373,459,261,286]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Jasione" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[373,459,261,286]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Jasione</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Westrich" authorityYear="1989" box="[473,657,260,287]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Campanulaceae</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Warncke" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[675,970,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Flavipanurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kastiliensis">
<emphasis box="[675,970,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Flavipanurgus kastiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1250,1345,260,286]" name="Portugal" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Portugal</collectingCountry>
with 13 confirmed records from Minho and Tr√°s-os-montes provinces between 
<date box="[1002,1173,296,323]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" value="2014" valueMax="2019">2014 and 2019</date>
, and the species can be easily found in northern hilly areas wherever 
<taxonomicName box="[707,782,332,358]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[707,782,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Sedum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species grow in abundance.
</paragraph>
